President Obama announced his intent to nominate John Berry as Director of the Office of Personnel Management and Julius Genachowski as Chairman of the Federal Communications Commission. President Obama praised Berry for his effective management in previous public service roles and expressed confidence in his ability to lead OPM. He also praised Genachowski's diverse and unparalleled experience in communications and technology and his deep appreciation for the country. Berry has a background in legislative work and management, having served as Deputy Assistant Secretary and acting Assistant Secretary for Law Enforcement at the Department of Treasury and as Assistant Secretary for Policy, Management, and Budget in the Clinton administration. He also worked as Director of the National Fish and Wildlife Foundation and successfully turned around the National Zoo. Genachowski, on the other hand, has experience as a technology executive and entrepreneur, as well as in government, having served at the Federal Communications Commission as Chief Counsel and as a law clerk for U.S. Supreme Court Justices David H. Souter and William J. Brennan, Jr. He has a J.D. from Harvard Law School and a B.A. from Columbia College.